1
00:01:43,750 --> 00:01:46,708
♪

2
00:01:46,791 --> 00:01:49,541
[leaves rustling]

3
00:01:51,500 --> 00:01:53,041
[gasp]

4
00:01:55,416 --> 00:01:56,833
[muffled]
Are you okay?

5
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:01,583
[REI]
When I awoke,

6
00:02:01,666 --> 00:02:04,875
I didn’t know how long
my slumber had lasted.

7
00:02:07,083 --> 00:02:08,875
Uh, hi there.

8
00:02:10,416 --> 00:02:13,166
And, to be honest,
I didn’t care.

9
00:02:13,250 --> 00:02:14,791
All that mattered in that moment

10
00:02:14,875 --> 00:02:17,041
was the awkward little boy.

11
00:02:17,125 --> 00:02:19,833
His eyed filled
with concern and wonder.

12
00:02:20,791 --> 00:02:23,333
Hey. D’you need some help?

13
00:02:25,250 --> 00:02:27,583
Who are you, boy?

14
00:02:28,541 --> 00:02:29,791
Oh, right!

15
00:02:29,875 --> 00:02:31,333
My name is Suigin!

16
00:02:32,833 --> 00:02:34,208
Hi, Suigin.

17
00:02:34,291 --> 00:02:35,916
Hi! [laugh]

18
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:37,041
What’s your name?

19
00:02:39,041 --> 00:02:40,916
You have one, right?

20
00:02:42,875 --> 00:02:44,750
[REI]
My name is...

21
00:02:48,708 --> 00:02:51,666
♪

22
00:02:51,750 --> 00:02:53,791
[shimmer]

23
00:02:56,166 --> 00:02:58,416
Look at ‘em.
Aren’t they beautiful?

24
00:02:58,500 --> 00:03:00,000
Sure...

25
00:03:00,083 --> 00:03:01,041
if you like creepy.

26
00:03:01,125 --> 00:03:02,083
[typing]

27
00:03:02,166 --> 00:03:03,875
Do we have to be out here?

28
00:03:03,958 --> 00:03:05,500
I mean, there’s nobody around.

29
00:03:05,583 --> 00:03:08,041
That’s the point, silly.
No one knows about this spot.

30
00:03:08,125 --> 00:03:10,083
-[BOY] You’re not making sense.
-[seductive saxophone music]

31
00:03:10,166 --> 00:03:12,000
[GIRL]
Does this make sense?

32
00:03:12,083 --> 00:03:13,416
[BOY struggling]
Hey!

33
00:03:13,500 --> 00:03:14,625
-[gasp]
-[can rattling]

34
00:03:14,708 --> 00:03:15,666
What the hell?

35
00:03:15,750 --> 00:03:16,958
Relax.

36
00:03:17,041 --> 00:03:18,583
No one’ll find us.

37
00:03:18,666 --> 00:03:20,416
-I’m-- I’m not ready!
-[GIRL] Now, close your eyes.

38
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:22,000
-[moaning]
-No, don’t!

39
00:03:22,083 --> 00:03:23,750
Hey, knock it off!

40
00:03:23,833 --> 00:03:24,666
[gasp]

41
00:03:24,750 --> 00:03:26,958
-Uh--
-[whimpering]

42
00:03:27,041 --> 00:03:28,000
What now?

43
00:03:28,083 --> 00:03:31,125
♪

44
00:03:33,958 --> 00:03:36,166
[deep voice]
Hello there.

45
00:03:36,250 --> 00:03:38,708
[screaming]

46
00:03:38,791 --> 00:03:39,750
[cans rattle]

47
00:03:39,833 --> 00:03:41,541
[panting, crying]

48
00:03:42,500 --> 00:03:44,458
Aww... They left.

49
00:03:44,541 --> 00:03:47,291
And they made another mess.
[sigh]

50
00:03:47,375 --> 00:03:48,416
[air hisses]

51
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:49,875
Meow.

52
00:03:49,958 --> 00:03:51,291
There.

53
00:03:51,375 --> 00:03:52,666
[gate rattles]

54
00:03:52,750 --> 00:03:54,208
[sigh]
Easy peasy.

55
00:03:54,291 --> 00:03:56,083
-[meowing]
-This job’s pretty great.

56
00:03:56,166 --> 00:03:58,791
As long as no punks come
out here, it’s super chill.

57
00:04:00,333 --> 00:04:01,541
Not to mention,

58
00:04:01,625 --> 00:04:02,791
free electricity.

59
00:04:02,875 --> 00:04:04,666
-[meowing]
-I get to relax outside

60
00:04:04,750 --> 00:04:06,875
and game as much as I want.

61
00:04:06,958 --> 00:04:08,333
Alright!

62
00:04:08,416 --> 00:04:10,541
Time for... adventure!

63
00:04:10,625 --> 00:04:11,583
[power on noise]

64
00:04:11,666 --> 00:04:13,541
[medieval-style music]

65
00:04:14,500 --> 00:04:15,875
[flames roar]

66
00:04:18,666 --> 00:04:21,208
♪

67
00:04:21,291 --> 00:04:23,833
[roar]

68
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:30,500
[swiping, thudding]

69
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:33,541
[crash]

70
00:04:34,958 --> 00:04:36,208
-[murmuring]
-Incredible!

71
00:04:36,291 --> 00:04:38,250
He beat the Ultimate Dragon
with one hit!

72
00:04:38,333 --> 00:04:40,666
And look at his equipment!
It’s just starter gear!

73
00:04:40,750 --> 00:04:43,166
Sounds like you noobs
need some educating.

74
00:04:43,250 --> 00:04:45,250
He’s a lone wolf
of immense skill

75
00:04:45,333 --> 00:04:47,500
who’s never uttered
a single word!

76
00:04:47,583 --> 00:04:48,750
He comes and goes,

77
00:04:48,833 --> 00:04:50,416
helping players when
they need it most

78
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:53,041
and never asks for
anything in return.

79
00:04:53,125 --> 00:04:56,291
The amazing Gwin!

80
00:04:56,375 --> 00:04:57,208
[chuckle]

81
00:04:57,291 --> 00:04:59,458
Aww... No biggie!

82
00:04:59,541 --> 00:05:00,958
-[triumphant music]
-Oh!

83
00:05:01,041 --> 00:05:02,708
Sweet, I leveled up again!

84
00:05:02,791 --> 00:05:03,708
[clicking]

85
00:05:03,791 --> 00:05:05,625
I mean, I’m nothing special.

86
00:05:05,708 --> 00:05:07,708
I just spend every second
of my free time playing.

87
00:05:08,666 --> 00:05:11,416
Let’s see.
Which dungeon should I hit next?

88
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:14,458
[GIRL screaming]
Someone help me!

89
00:05:14,541 --> 00:05:15,375
The heck?

90
00:05:15,458 --> 00:05:16,875
No!

91
00:05:16,958 --> 00:05:18,375
[roaring, laughing]

92
00:05:18,458 --> 00:05:19,833
Back off creep!

93
00:05:19,916 --> 00:05:21,750
-[grunt]
-[energy roaring]

94
00:05:22,750 --> 00:05:24,583
-[grunt]
-[explosions]

95
00:05:24,666 --> 00:05:25,583
[roaring]

96
00:05:25,666 --> 00:05:27,875
-[laughing]
-[screaming]

97
00:05:27,958 --> 00:05:30,250
[sigh]
Geez.

98
00:05:30,333 --> 00:05:33,375
Using water based attacks won’t
do anything to a Kick Backer.

99
00:05:33,458 --> 00:05:35,541
For these...

100
00:05:35,625 --> 00:05:36,625
[clicking]

101
00:05:36,708 --> 00:05:38,333
[energy rushing]

102
00:05:38,416 --> 00:05:39,208
-[explosion]
-[roar]

103
00:05:39,291 --> 00:05:41,041
[roaring]

104
00:05:41,125 --> 00:05:42,416
you use ice.

105
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:43,458
[smash]

106
00:05:43,541 --> 00:05:44,541
-[roar]
-And hit ‘em hard!

107
00:05:44,625 --> 00:05:45,875
[explosion]

108
00:05:47,875 --> 00:05:49,916
[sparkling]

109
00:05:51,041 --> 00:05:52,458
[scarf flapping]

110
00:05:53,500 --> 00:05:55,041
[GIRL]
Wow!

111
00:05:55,125 --> 00:05:56,875
[staff clanging]

112
00:05:56,958 --> 00:05:59,583
Hey... Thanks a lot!

113
00:05:59,666 --> 00:06:00,625
That was close.

114
00:06:00,708 --> 00:06:02,375
If you hadn’t come along,

115
00:06:02,458 --> 00:06:04,125
I don’t know what
I would have done.

116
00:06:04,208 --> 00:06:05,708
So, uh,

117
00:06:05,791 --> 00:06:08,000
my name’s Ray.
Wanna be friends?

118
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:10,750
-What’s your--
-[electrical short]

119
00:06:10,833 --> 00:06:11,666
Huh?

120
00:06:11,750 --> 00:06:13,250
♪

121
00:06:13,333 --> 00:06:14,541
[gasp]

122
00:06:14,625 --> 00:06:16,791
No, no, no, no!
Not now! Not now!

123
00:06:16,875 --> 00:06:18,708
-What happened?!
-[yawn]

124
00:06:20,791 --> 00:06:22,375
[sigh]

125
00:06:23,375 --> 00:06:25,250
Only one thing I can think of.

126
00:06:26,416 --> 00:06:27,666
Ran outta juice.

127
00:06:27,750 --> 00:06:29,916
[fizzling]

128
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:32,083
-Meow, meow!
-[metal rattling]

129
00:06:32,166 --> 00:06:34,708
Don’t worry, Wanchoi,
I’ll be fine!

130
00:06:34,791 --> 00:06:37,708
A little wire work,
and we’re good to go.

131
00:06:37,791 --> 00:06:39,958
It was incredible! I mean it.

132
00:06:40,041 --> 00:06:41,291
He was so amazing!

133
00:06:41,375 --> 00:06:43,750
The boss character
was super strong,

134
00:06:43,833 --> 00:06:47,125
but he just swooped right in
and beat it like it was nothing!

135
00:06:47,208 --> 00:06:50,375
♪

136
00:06:51,333 --> 00:06:52,333
Hey.

137
00:06:53,291 --> 00:06:54,333
Hey.

138
00:07:02,250 --> 00:07:04,291
[bang]

139
00:07:07,125 --> 00:07:09,291
-[crash, tumble]
-Oh! Whoa! Ow!

140
00:07:09,375 --> 00:07:10,958
[groan]

141
00:07:11,916 --> 00:07:13,041
You lecher!

142
00:07:13,125 --> 00:07:15,333
-[groaning]
-Idiot! Pervert deluxe!

143
00:07:15,416 --> 00:07:17,666
How dare you!

144
00:07:20,625 --> 00:07:23,125
-[bell chiming]
-[student chatter]

145
00:07:24,083 --> 00:07:25,375
[typing]

146
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:27,583
[squirt]

147
00:07:27,666 --> 00:07:28,791
[squeak]

148
00:07:28,875 --> 00:07:29,916
[wince]

149
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:31,125
Ow!

150
00:07:32,458 --> 00:07:34,875
Whatever happened to
the “benefit of the doubt?”

151
00:07:34,958 --> 00:07:38,458
Though, I guess if I were them,
I’d have freaked out, too.

152
00:07:38,541 --> 00:07:39,916
-[GIRL] Wow, Rei.
-Uh.

153
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:41,541
You must like that game.

154
00:07:41,625 --> 00:07:43,416
-You can’t put it down.
-[REI] I do!

155
00:07:43,500 --> 00:07:45,916
But, my father made it,
so I might be biased.

156
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,291
[GIRL]
Makes sense.

157
00:07:47,375 --> 00:07:50,250
You’re a textbook
daddy’s girl, Rei Riku.

158
00:07:50,333 --> 00:07:51,250
Stop it. [giggle]

159
00:07:51,333 --> 00:07:52,958
But, you know,

160
00:07:53,041 --> 00:07:54,833
this world is special.

161
00:07:54,916 --> 00:07:57,583
Something about it makes
me feel like I belong.

162
00:07:57,666 --> 00:08:00,000
Whenever I play it,
reality fades away.

163
00:08:00,083 --> 00:08:02,625
You feel like you belong, huh?

164
00:08:02,708 --> 00:08:05,916
Kinda funny, considering
how much you suck at it.

165
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:07,958
-Hey! Don’t be so mean!
-[giggle]

166
00:08:08,041 --> 00:08:09,125
-[moan]
-[GIRL] Just kidding!

167
00:08:09,208 --> 00:08:10,666
[REI]
Geez.

168
00:08:11,625 --> 00:08:13,333
Ah, love. How sweet.

169
00:08:13,416 --> 00:08:14,416
What the--

170
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:15,666
Ranshou?

171
00:08:15,750 --> 00:08:16,750
[chuckle]

172
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:19,500
Don’t worry. I’m not judging.

173
00:08:19,583 --> 00:08:20,875
It’s just...

174
00:08:20,958 --> 00:08:23,333
Keep in mind who it is
you’re falling for.

175
00:08:24,291 --> 00:08:26,333
She might as well be an idol
to the boys in this school.

176
00:08:26,416 --> 00:08:27,250
[sigh]

177
00:08:27,333 --> 00:08:28,708
[chatter]

178
00:08:28,791 --> 00:08:30,416
[RANSHOU] I’m worried that
if you try to reach

179
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:33,250
a star that shines as brightly
as she does, the way Icarus did,

180
00:08:33,333 --> 00:08:34,541
[moan]

181
00:08:34,625 --> 00:08:36,750
you’ll get burned
and fall to your doom.

182
00:08:36,833 --> 00:08:39,458
[GIRL]
Back off, creeps! Let’s go.

183
00:08:39,541 --> 00:08:40,666
-[BOY] Hey! Hold on!
-[gasp]

184
00:08:40,750 --> 00:08:43,333
-Don’t run away!
-Please, Rei Riku!

185
00:08:43,416 --> 00:08:45,125
Hey, wait a second.

186
00:08:45,208 --> 00:08:47,000
That name.
Is she the one who...

187
00:08:47,083 --> 00:08:48,708
Of course.

188
00:08:48,791 --> 00:08:51,541
That jerk.
Saying whatever he wants.

189
00:08:51,625 --> 00:08:53,000
It isn’t like that!

190
00:08:53,083 --> 00:08:55,250
I just...

191
00:08:55,333 --> 00:08:56,291
[sigh]

192
00:08:56,375 --> 00:08:57,541
[chatter]

193
00:08:57,625 --> 00:09:00,166
I don’t know. I just...

194
00:09:01,708 --> 00:09:02,750
[click]

195
00:09:03,916 --> 00:09:04,833
[click]

196
00:09:07,666 --> 00:09:09,125
[SUIGIN]
Whatever.

197
00:09:09,208 --> 00:09:12,416
At least there’s one thing
I can take comfort in.

198
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:13,833
[typing]

199
00:09:17,583 --> 00:09:20,041
Getting stronger
in game is all I need.

200
00:09:20,125 --> 00:09:21,333
[sipping]

201
00:09:21,416 --> 00:09:22,416
-[chime]
-Uh?

202
00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:24,375
-Hey, Gwin, how are you?
-[spit]

203
00:09:24,458 --> 00:09:25,916
[coughing]

204
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:28,250
[RAY] I really appreciate
you saving me the other day.

205
00:09:28,333 --> 00:09:30,583
It meant a lot.
Wanna play together?

206
00:09:30,666 --> 00:09:31,958
-Huh?
-I think it would be fun!

207
00:09:32,916 --> 00:09:35,000
I hope to hear from you soon!

208
00:09:35,083 --> 00:09:36,041
[giggle]

209
00:09:36,125 --> 00:09:37,083
[chime]

210
00:09:38,041 --> 00:09:39,166
[gasp]

211
00:09:40,333 --> 00:09:41,875
-[sigh]
-[hissing]

212
00:09:42,833 --> 00:09:45,000
No way!

213
00:09:45,083 --> 00:09:47,000
[rattling bottles]

214
00:09:47,083 --> 00:09:48,750
[bicycle wheels clicking]

215
00:09:49,708 --> 00:09:51,166
[SUIGIN] For the next
several months,

216
00:09:52,125 --> 00:09:53,583
♪

217
00:09:53,666 --> 00:09:56,041
the time she and I spent
together seemed like a dream.

218
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:59,291
-[RAY giggling]
-Being in the game.

219
00:09:59,375 --> 00:10:00,833
Being with her.

220
00:10:01,791 --> 00:10:02,666
-[giggle]
-I thought that

221
00:10:02,750 --> 00:10:03,916
was all I needed.

222
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,458
♪

223
00:10:05,541 --> 00:10:06,958
But, then...

224
00:10:07,958 --> 00:10:09,416
[RAY]
Hey, Gwin.

225
00:10:11,416 --> 00:10:13,333
What are you like
outside of the game?

226
00:10:13,416 --> 00:10:16,958
I’ve been thinking about
that for awhile now.

227
00:10:17,041 --> 00:10:18,625
[breeze blowing]

228
00:10:18,708 --> 00:10:21,416
I’d love to meet
the real you someday.

229
00:10:21,500 --> 00:10:23,250
What do you think?

230
00:10:24,791 --> 00:10:26,375
-[brakes squeak]
-[grunt]

231
00:10:26,458 --> 00:10:28,375
[sigh]

232
00:10:28,458 --> 00:10:30,458
[laughing]

233
00:10:31,416 --> 00:10:33,583
[bicycle wheels clicking]

234
00:10:33,666 --> 00:10:35,250
[SUIGIN]
Of course,

235
00:10:35,333 --> 00:10:36,375
we could never meet.

236
00:10:36,458 --> 00:10:37,583
[water running]

237
00:10:37,666 --> 00:10:39,583
Because in the real world...

238
00:10:39,666 --> 00:10:41,875
I’m swamped with part-time jobs.

239
00:10:41,958 --> 00:10:44,833
I’m a poor student
with no family.

240
00:10:44,916 --> 00:10:47,833
[snoring]

241
00:10:47,916 --> 00:10:49,416
-[bottles rattling]
-[bicycle wheels clicking]

242
00:10:49,500 --> 00:10:51,500
We live in completely
different worlds.

243
00:10:51,583 --> 00:10:52,875
[GIRL]
It's true!

244
00:10:52,958 --> 00:10:54,208
-[laughing]
-[SUIGIN] I’m an awkward nerd.

245
00:10:54,291 --> 00:10:55,500
-[laughing]
-[GIRL] Really!

246
00:10:55,583 --> 00:10:58,000
[SUIGIN]
You’re a shining star.

247
00:10:58,083 --> 00:11:01,041
♪

248
00:11:01,125 --> 00:11:02,000
So...

249
00:11:02,083 --> 00:11:03,208
[fire crackling]

250
00:11:05,833 --> 00:11:07,458
When we’re inside the game,

251
00:11:10,208 --> 00:11:11,833
grant me one wish.

252
00:11:11,916 --> 00:11:14,458
Let me stay with you.

253
00:11:17,458 --> 00:11:19,333
That’s all I want.

254
00:11:19,416 --> 00:11:21,958
To be here with you, forever.

255
00:11:22,041 --> 00:11:24,875
[fire roaring]

256
00:11:24,958 --> 00:11:27,000
I think that would
be enough for me.

257
00:11:30,291 --> 00:11:31,458
[beep]

258
00:11:31,541 --> 00:11:32,541
[gasp]

259
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:36,125
They’re shutting
it down for good?

260
00:11:36,208 --> 00:11:38,125
[sob]

261
00:11:38,208 --> 00:11:40,791
-[wail]
-Meow!

262
00:13:15,541 --> 00:13:18,083
[SUIGIN]
The Silver Guardian!

